    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-03-18T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-03-18T23:00:00-05:00" n="176"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d176">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 PW/3–1345: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-03-19T00:00:00-04:00"
                            >March 19, 1945—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1090. Your 1196, March 13. French Embassy has left with us three notes<note
                        n="14" xml:id="d176fn1">Reference is to notes Nos. 303, 304, and 332, dated
                        March 12; No. 332 is not printed.</note> asking (1) that military
                    assistance, including dropping of arms, medicine and supplies, be extended to
                    the resistance forces in Indo-China; (2) that we conclude a civil affairs
                    agreement for that area and (3) that General Blaizot<note n="15"
                        xml:id="d176fn2">Gen. Roger Blaizot, head of French military mission at
                        Kandy.</note> be accredited to General Wedemeyer for liaison purposes.</p>
                <p>All three proposals are under study by Joint Chiefs of Staff.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
